Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise, then slice into shreds. Halve, peel, and dice @red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced). Mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Halve @marble potatoes{12%ounce}(halved).

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a large pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Make sure all are cut-side down. Roast until golden brown and crispy, ~{18-20%minutes}, tossing once halfway through.

== Hash ==

Heat @butter{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add onions and toss until just softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce} and garlic, and toss until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @cayenne pepper{1%teaspoon}. Add Brussels sprouts, and toss until veggies are tender and beginning to turn golden brown, another ~{4-5%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove pan from heat.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in another large pan over medium-high heat. Once hot, crack @eggs{4} and fry until edges begin to turn golden. Reduce heat to medium, and cover until whites are set but yolks are still runny, about ~{1%minute}.

> TIP: Add a few teaspoons water to speed up cooking.

Toss potatoes into Brussels sprout mixture. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Divide hash between two plates, and top with fried eggs. Sprinkle with salt and a pinch of cayenne pepper (to taste). Enjoy!